Subject: [PATCH] kanidm: 8h OAuth2 access tokens + refresh-token reuse grace

Two carried patches that together stop the Envoy-Gateway/kanidm logout loop.
Envoy's oauth2 filter is stateless and cannot single-flight refreshes; kanidm's
refresh-token reuse check is strict single-use with no grace. With 15m access
tokens, SPA backends behind the gateway refresh constantly, fan concurrent
same-token refreshes across replicas, and trip reuse detection -> session
destroyed -> user logged out. Both constants are compile-time and not
configurable in kanidm 1.10.4 (proven from source).

(B) constants/mod.rs: OAUTH2_ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRY 15m -> 8h. The proxy then
    almost never refreshes mid-session. Revocation latency rises to <=8h
    (accepted posture trade-off).
(A) idm/oauth2.rs: tolerate a 60s grace in the refresh reuse check so the rare
    concurrent refresh of a just-rotated token is not misdetected as reuse.
    Genuinely stale tokens still nuke the session.

Only .rs files change, so the vendored cargoDeps hash is unaffected.
---
diff --git a/server/lib/src/constants/mod.rs b/server/lib/src/constants/mod.rs
index 1840dc9..1824dd1 100644
--- a/server/lib/src/constants/mod.rs
+++ b/server/lib/src/constants/mod.rs
@@ -185,7 +185,13 @@ pub const OAUTH_REFRESH_TOKEN_EXPIRY: u32 = 3600 * 16;
 
 /// How long access tokens should last. This is NOT the length
 /// of the refresh token, which is bound to the issuing session.
-pub const OAUTH2_ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRY: u32 = 15 * 60;
+//
+// nix-config patch: raised from 15m to 8h. The Envoy Gateway oauth2 filter is
+// stateless and cannot single-flight refreshes; with 15m tokens its SPA backends
+// refresh constantly and race kanidm's single-use refresh-token reuse check. An
+// 8h access token means the proxy almost never refreshes mid-session. Paired with
+// the refresh reuse-grace patch in idm/oauth2.rs.
+pub const OAUTH2_ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRY: u32 = 8 * 60 * 60;
 
 /// The amount of time a suppliers clock can be "ahead" before
 /// we warn about possible clock synchronisation issues.
diff --git a/server/lib/src/idm/oauth2.rs b/server/lib/src/idm/oauth2.rs
index 7e2ad23..0512c48 100644
--- a/server/lib/src/idm/oauth2.rs
+++ b/server/lib/src/idm/oauth2.rs
@@ -1653,7 +1653,14 @@ impl IdmServerProxyWriteTransaction<'_> {
                 // this indicates session desync / replay. We must nuke the session at this point.
                 //
                 // Need to think about how to handle this nicely give transactions.
-                if iat < oauth2_session.issued_at.unix_timestamp() {
+                //
+                // nix-config patch: tolerate a short grace window so that concurrent refreshes
+                // carrying the SAME just-rotated refresh token (e.g. parallel XHRs fanned across
+                // multiple stateless Envoy gateway replicas that cannot single-flight) are not
+                // misdetected as reuse and do not destroy the session. This is the OAuth2 Security
+                // BCP refresh-token rotation grace. Genuinely stale tokens (issued more than the
+                // grace before the session's issued_at) still trip reuse detection and nuke it.
+                if iat < oauth2_session.issued_at.unix_timestamp() - 60 {
                     security_info!(
                         ?session_id,
                         "Attempt to reuse a refresh token detected, destroying session"
